Titolo: Grendel's Cave

Anno: 1998

Descrizione: Grendel's Cave is a real-time browser-based role-playing video game and MUD.  Grendel Enterprises published and ran it exclusively on the Internet.  The basis for Grendelâ€™s Cave was Anglo-Saxon mythology and Beowulf, and it is set in the historical medieval period.  Scholars consider it an artistic depiction of Grendel and the poem, Beowulf, as well as a modern adaptation and a derivative work of the epic.  Educational websites use Grendel's Cave as an Internet learning aid for medieval literature and they considered it an online Beowulf resource.